Role & Permission Hardening Rules for Agency OS

Scope:
- role clarification
- permission matrix
- navigation visibility
- page/route access
- action/button visibility
- server-side permission enforcement
- scoped query protection

Hard rules:
- do not add new features
- do not redesign UI
- do not change business logic except for access control enforcement
- do not expand architecture unnecessarily
- work one RBAC stage at a time
- stop after the active stage and provide a completion report

Roles to enforce strictly:
- admin / owner
- coordinator
- reviewer
- member / freelancer

Non-negotiable:
- UI hiding alone is NOT sufficient
- route protection alone is NOT sufficient
- server-side enforcement must exist for restricted mutations
- scoped roles must not receive unauthorized data
